EXTENDED OUTLOOK
WEDNESDAY TO SATURDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 112300 UTC
ON WEDNESDAY AN AREA OF HIGH PRESSURE IS EXP TO BE CENTRED SW OF THE UK
WHILST A LOW LIES IN THE N NORWEGIAN BASIN. OVERNIGHT AND THROUGH THURSDAY
THIS LOW IS FCST TO SLWY FILL AND MOV NEWARDS ALLOWING THE HIGH TO EDGE
CLOSER TO THE UK WITH A LIKELY CENTRE OF 1022 ACROSS SW IRELAND MIDDAY FRIDAY.
MEANWHILE A SMALL LOW IS FCST TO DEVELOP OFF THE COAST OF PORTUGAL AND AN
ATLANTIC LOW PRESSURE SYSTEM BECOMES SLOW MOV SE OF GREENLAND. ON SATURDAY
THE HIGH IS EXP TO BECOME CENTRED OVER THE UK WITH LOWS SW FITZROY AND W
OF ICELAND. STRG WINDS ARE INITIALLY EXP ACROSS THE N OF CULLERCOATS. THESE
ARE FCST TO BECOME CONFINED TO UTSIRE FISHER AND THE N OF GERMAN BIGHT ON
THURSDAY. WINDS ARE EXP TO EASE THURSDAY EVENING WITH NO FURTHER HAZARDOUS
WINDS LIKELY THROUGH THE REST OF THE PERIOD
